    <h1>DX, SPACE & DORA</h1>
    
    <div class="page-intro">
        <p>
            Understanding developer experience frameworks: DORA metrics for delivery performance, 
            SPACE framework for productivity, and DevEx for developer satisfaction and effectiveness.
        </p>
    </div>

    <section>
        <h2>DORA Metrics</h2>
        <p>
            DevOps Research and Assessment (DORA) identified four key metrics that indicate software 
            delivery performance.
        </p>
        <h3>The Four Key Metrics</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Deployment Frequency:</strong> How often does your organization deploy code to production?</li>
            <li><strong>Lead Time for Changes:</strong> How long does it take to go from code commit to production?</li>
            <li><strong>Mean Time to Recovery (MTTR):</strong> How long does it take to restore service after an incident?</li>
            <li><strong>Change Failure Rate:</strong> What percentage of changes result in degraded service?</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>SPACE Framework</h2>
        <p>
            SPACE is a framework that captures the multidimensional nature of developer productivity.
        </p>
        <h3>The Five Dimensions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>S - Satisfaction & Well-being:</strong> How fulfilled developers feel with their work</li>
            <li><strong>P - Performance:</strong> The outcomes of a system or process</li>
            <li><strong>A - Activity:</strong> Counts of actions or outputs completed</li>
            <li><strong>C - Communication & Collaboration:</strong> How people and teams work together</li>
            <li><strong>E - Efficiency & Flow:</strong> The ability to complete work with minimal interruptions</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Developer Experience (DevEx/DX)</h2>
        <p>
            DevEx represents a paradigm shift from focusing solely on productivity outcomes to focusing on 
            how developers experience their work.
        </p>
        <h3>The Three Core Dimensions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Cognitive Load:</strong> The mental effort required to complete tasks</li>
            <li><strong>Feedback Loops:</strong> The speed at which developers can validate their work</li>
            <li><strong>Flow State:</strong> The ability to achieve and maintain focus on complex tasks</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
